Police operatives attached to the Railway Command have arrested three suspected armed vandals along the Ameka/Mbom rail track in Umuahia, Abia State. The suspects identified as Kelechi Ononiwu, 36, Kalu Egbe, 30, Stanley, 27, were apprehended after a gun battle with operatives who received information from the public about their activity. They were said to have been found removing rail sleepers and loading them into a black Toyota Hiace bus. Police sources said the five suspects opened fire on the operatives but were overpowered. Three of them were arrested.   Davido disburses N250m to 292 orphanages in 27 States     I won’t defect, I won’t go to court, says…     FULL LIST: 292 orphanages that got Davido’s 250m gift   - Advertisement - One of them was said to have sustained gunshot injury and was being treated at Federal Medical Center Umuahia. - Advertisement - Confirming the incident, Commissioner of Police, Railway, Mrs. Yetunde Longe, said the command had started searching for the fleeing suspects. CP Longe dismissed reports that  a train was halted by unknown persons around Abeokuta on the Lagos-Ibadan corridor on February 12, causing panic among passengers. She described the news as fake, insisting that the railways were safe for travellers. “In order to avoid possible derailment or accident that could lead to casualties, he had to stop and reposition the track before proceeding on the said trip,” she said. SPONSORED